AB  - With the deep integration of 'Internet Plus' and modern agriculture, cloud-based agricultural technology service platforms have become vital for improving production efficiency and precision management. This paper aims to build an agricultural technology service cloud platform that supports multi-source data fusion and real-time interaction, and proposes a spatiotemporal feature-based personalized recommendation algorithm. First, we design a unified spatiotemporal data model and implement online data acquisition and preprocessing mechanisms for heterogeneous sources such as weather, soil, remote sensing imagery, and agricultural operation records. Next, we introduce spatial and temporal weight factors according to farmers' planting habits and regional characteristics, combining collaborative filtering with content-based recommendation to form a spatiotemporally weighted hybrid recommendation framework. Finally, we deploy and test the system on typical experimental plots of wheat and rice. Comparative experiments show that our algorithm improves recommendation accuracy by 12.7% and timeliness by 18.3% compared with traditional methods, effectively meeting farmers' demands for precise agricultural decision support. These results offer a technical reference for enhancing functionality and intelligence in agricultural service platforms, and lay the groundwork for extending to more crops and complex scenarios. © 2025 IEEE.
