AB  - In this paper, we present approaches for efficient linking, discovery and integration of spatial as well as non-spatial data in a spatial data infrastructure (SDI). Geoportals act as main gateways to SDIs. Due to semantic heterogeneity issues they are facing challenges in regard to linking, discovery and integration of digital (geospatial) resources. Thus, we enrich resource descriptions with synonyms, toponyms und translated terms based on multilingual thesauri and ontologies. Therefore, users can discover resources that differ from the search language and context of the user. Besides the actual search results, users get recommendations of geo-spatial and non-spatial resources that may be of interest to them. These recommendations are based on the search experience of other users as well as automatically derived similarities of their textual descriptions.
