AB  - The POI (Point-of-interest) recommendation system is based on location-based network services, which enables users to share real-time geographic information through check-in behaviors and punch records in network services. In this paper, the POI recommendation algorithm is improved, which mainly includes the following three aspects: (1) putting forward a weight adjustment method based on time and geographical factors in the process of computing similarity and conducting experimental investigations; (2) introducing the EbbingHaus forgetting curve in psychology and proposing the nonlinear forgetting function; (3) investigating slope one algorithm in the POI recommendation system, as well as the nearest neighbor model, and presenting an improved nearest neighbor slope one algorithm based on user preferences. Experiments show that our algorithm can greatly improve the accuracy of POI recommendation. © 2018 IEEE.
