AB  - This paper innovatively proposes an algorithm named User-Spatial Multilayer Filtering (U-SMF), which is specifically applied to the research of e-commerce personalized recommendation algorithms based on User behavior data. The algorithm cleverly integrates three technologies: User-Based Collaborative Filtering (UBCF), Multilayer Perceptron (MLP) and Spatial Attention Mechanism (SAM). It aims to comprehensively improve the accuracy and efficiency of recommendations. U-SMF first captures similarities between users through the UBCF to generate an initial recommendation list. Then, the multilayer neural network structure of MLP is used to further enhance the characterization ability of the model and make the recommendation results more diversified. At the same time, the algorithm also introduces the SAM mechanism, which can capture the spatial correlation of user behavior data and make the recommendation more suitable to the actual needs of users. In the experimental part, we compare U-SMF with traditional recommendation algorithm. The results show that U-SMF can more accurately capture user preferences, significantly reduce recommendation errors, and significantly improve the user experience. This firmly establishes the practicality and effectiveness of the framework within the domain of personalized recommendation algorithms in e-commerce, utilizing user behavior data. © 2025 IEEE.
